Charlotte Mokoena has been appointed Sasol human resources (HR) and corporate affairs executive VP, effective February 1, 2017. As part of the group executive committee, she will direct and oversee Sasol&rsquo;s global HR and corporate affairs functions in line with the group&rsquo;s strategic aims. She is currently HR executive at Tongaat Hulett. &ldquo;Charlotte has worked in both the private and NGO sectors covering the beverage, information and communication technology, education and agricultural industries. We look forward to benefiting from her vast experience and expertise,&rdquo; said Sasol joint president and CEO Stephen Cornell in a statement.